What is a good example of a time management strategy for someone who works remotely?
A good example of a time management strategy for someone who works remotely would be to create a daily schedule and stick to it. For instance, they could start each morning with a specific task like answering emails or working on projects that require more concentration, followed by lighter tasks during the afternoon when their energy levels might be lower. This way, they ensure that all tasks get completed on time while also giving themselves breaks throughout the day so as not to burn out too quickly!
